M2 Brownign 50 has been standard military heavy machine
gun for many years. The large calliber machineguns are
in genera the best weapon agains robust and 
physically resilient other sides infantry. This new 
version is modified to use larger cartriges 
(12.7x120 mm) instead of commonly used (12.7x99 mm),
which gives the gun increased range. This new amunition
is manufactured almost entirely as JHP (jacketed hollow
point), which has a devastating effect on living tissue
upon impact.
